1. Project Overview
This project develops an AI system capable of detecting potholes in road images and videos and assessing their severity using instance segmentation. The system is built using the YOLOv8 segmentation model and deployed through a Streamlit-based web application that allows users to upload images or videos for pothole detection.
The application performs pothole detection, severity estimation based on area coverage, risk analysis, and generates downloadable reports for infrastructure monitoring.
The goal of the system is to support smart road monitoring and assist municipal authorities in prioritizing road maintenance.
________________________________________
2. Data Source
The dataset used for training the pothole detection model was obtained from publicly available road datasets and Roboflow dataset repositories.
Dataset characteristics
•	Road surface images containing potholes
•	Images captured from road cameras and vehicle-mounted cameras
•	Various lighting conditions (daylight, shadows, uneven surfaces)
Dataset statistics
•	Original dataset size: ~1,240 images
•	Image format: JPG / PNG
•	Annotation format: YOLOv8 segmentation format (.txt polygon coordinates)
________________________________________
3. Data Ingestion
The dataset was uploaded and managed through the Roboflow platform.
Steps performed during ingestion:
•	Images uploaded through Roboflow interface
•	Manual verification of pothole annotations
•	Polygon annotation used for precise pothole boundaries
•	Dataset exported in YOLOv8 segmentation format
•	Dataset downloaded to Google Colab for training
________________________________________
4. Data Cleaning & Preprocessing
The following preprocessing steps were performed before training:
• Removal of irrelevant or incorrectly labeled images
• Validation of polygon annotations for potholes
• Ensuring tight annotation boundaries around potholes
• Removal of cracks or non-pothole road defects
All images were resized to:
Input resolution: 640 × 640 pixels
This standardization ensures compatibility with YOLO training and improves training stability.
________________________________________
5. Data Augmentation
To improve model generalization and robustness, data augmentation was applied using Roboflow.
Applied augmentations
• Horizontal flip (50%)
• Random rotation (±10°)
• Brightness adjustment (±15%)
• Exposure adjustment (±15%)
• Gaussian blur (light)
• Random noise
• Camera gain variation
Dataset expansion
Original images: 1240
After augmentation: 9,052 images

Purpose:
•	Improve detection under different lighting conditions
•	Improve small pothole detection
•	Reduce overfitting
________________________________________
6. Dataset Versioning
Dataset versioning was maintained in Roboflow.
Version history
Version 1
Raw dataset upload with initial annotations
Version 2
Resized images and augmentation applied
Version 3
Annotation corrections and optimization
Each version is stored and reproducible through Roboflow dataset version control.
________________________________________
7. Data Splitting
The dataset was split automatically by Roboflow.
Training set: 70%
Validation set: 20%
Testing set: 10%
This split ensures proper model evaluation and prevents overfitting.
________________________________________
8. Model Training
The pothole detection model was trained using the Ultralytics YOLOv8 segmentation framework.
Model configuration
Model architecture: YOLOv8n-seg
Input size: 640 × 640
Epochs: 100
Early stopping: enabled
Batch size: 16
Training was conducted in Google Colab with GPU acceleration.
Evaluation metrics
Box mAP@50: 0.742
Mask mAP@50: 0.734
These metrics indicate the model’s ability to accurately detect and segment potholes.
________________________________________
9. Deployment
The trained model is deployed in a simulated driving environment through a Streamlit web application.
The system allows users to upload road images or videos and automatically detect potholes.
Application features
• Image pothole detection
• Video pothole detection
• Severity estimation based on pothole area
• Risk index calculation
• Infrastructure maintenance recommendation
• CSV result export
• PDF maintenance report generation
• Analytics dashboard
Outputs generated by the system
• Bounding box coordinates
• Segmentation masks
• Class label
• Confidence score
• Pothole area estimation
• Severity classification (Small / Medium / Large)
• Road risk index
